30/09/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano on Wednesday (29 September) urged for the establishment of a united front against drug trafficking, involving both institutions and the public. 
Speaking at a national anti-drug conference, he pledged zero tolerance for politicians who protect traffickers and others involved in organised crime.
Also Wednesday, human error was blamed for the 16 September crash of a MiG fighter during take-off from Mother Theresa International Airport in Tirana. 
The pilot was killed in the incident. 
(Albanian Daily News - 30/09/04; ATA - 29/09/04)
